description:
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for a Band 6 Specialist ASD Practitioner who will be based in the multi-disciplinary Autism Assessment Team. This is a permanent full time position, and is based in Exeter, and is open to practitioners who have experience and skills in autism assessment; and working with children and young people presenting with complex needs.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will join our specialist team, which is part of Children and Family Health Devon, at an exciting time of change. In this role you will work closely with other agencies; as well as other services within CFHD such as CAMHS, Occupational Therapy Learning Disabilities and Speech and Language Therapy.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will work within the Specialist Team to provide high quality assessment, and post diagnostic advice and support.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Experience in using assessment tools such as ADOS and 3DI would be an advantage.&lt;/p&gt;
